The number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in South Africa has passed the 10 000 mark. Health Minister Zweli Mkize said on Sunday that the total now stands at 10 015. The total number of deaths is now 194.  Theee were confitred in the Western Cape, one in the Eastern Cape and four in Gauteng. The number of recoveries was 4 173. The Western Cape and Eastern Cape combined make up 84% of the total new cases, Mkhize said.  341 336 tests have been conducted, with 49% of tests occurring in private facilities and 51% in public facilities. 17 257 tests had been conducted since the department's last report.  